## THE HONEST ACCOUNTING

Here's what we know about these four, according to *The Aviationist*: G-1 and G-2, dedicated ground-test articles, proving out the airframe under stress it'll never fly through. T-1, flying since November 2023, the one expanding the envelope. T-2, flying since September 2025, now deep into mission-systems and weapons-integration testing at Edwards.

G-1 and G-2 were both built to be tested to failure, not flown. That's the job. Neither will likely ever leave the ground.

*[SPECULATION — flagged]* Two more airframes are scheduled for delivery before the end of 2026. Nobody's confirmed exact months. If the production pace holds, a third airframe could plausibly be ready by October, a fourth by December — though nobody has said that. That's just the shape of the curve.

